<paragraph blockId="26.[683,1215,225,728]" pageId="26" pageNumber="26">
IDENTIFICATION: We consulted descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[931,1155,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscus">
<emphasis box="[931,1155,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="26">Platyrrhinus infuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera, A." box="[796,967,293,317]" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 308" refId="ref33659" refString="Cabrera, A. 1958. Catalogo de los mamiferos de America del Sur. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales &quot; Bernardino Rivadavia, &quot; Ciencias Zoologicas 4: 1 - 308." type="journal article" year="1958">Cabrera (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; D. C. Carter" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="72 - 82" refId="ref36022" refString="Gardner, A. L., and D. C. Carter. 1972. A review of the Peruvian species of Vampyrops (Chiroptera: Phyllostomatidae). Journal of Mammalogy, 53: 72 - 82." type="journal article" year="1972">Gardner and Carter (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Swanepoel, P. &amp; H. H. Genoways" box="[766,1118,328,352]" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 441" refId="ref42730" refString="Swanepoel, P., and H. H. Genoways. 1979. Morphometrics. In R. J. Baker, J. K. Jones, Jr., and D. C. Carter (editors), Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomatidae, Part III: 1 - 441. Special Publications, Texas Tech University Museum 16." type="journal article" year="1979">Swanepoel and Genoways (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Velazco, P. M." pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 53" refId="ref43109" refString="Velazco, P. M. 2005. Morphological phylogeny of the bat genus Platyrrhinus Saussure, 1860 (Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) with the description of four new species. Fieldiana Zoology, New Series 105: 1 - 53." type="book chapter" year="2005">Velazco (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Velazco, P. M. &amp; A. L. Gardner" box="[812,1114,362,386]" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="249 - 281" refId="ref43228" refString="Velazco, P. M., and A. L. Gardner. 2009. A new species of Platyrrhinus (Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) from western Colombia and Ecuador, with emended diagnoses of P. aquilus, P. dorsalis, and P. umbratus. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 122: 249 - 281." type="journal article" year="2009">Velazco and Gardner (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. No subspecies are currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gardner, 2008 d)" baseAuthorityName="Gardner" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscus">
<emphasis box="[1093,1212,396,420]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="26">P. infuscus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L." box="[691,858,430,454]" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="329 - 342" refId="ref35907" refString="Gardner, A. L. 2008 d (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Platyrrhinus Saussure, 1860. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 329 - 342. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gardner, 2008d</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Our Mayo River basin specimens exhibit the diagnostic characteristics of the species: larger size (FA&gt; 
<quantity box="[854,931,498,522]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="54.0">54 mm</quantity>
); dark brown dorsal pelage; facial and dorsal stripes inconspicuous; short, sparse hair on the upper surface of feet; posterolabial cuspulid present on p5; M1 parastyle present; and m1 metaconid well developed (
<bibRefCitation author="Velazco, P. M." box="[965,1111,635,659]" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 53" refId="ref43109" refString="Velazco, P. M. 2005. Morphological phylogeny of the bat genus Platyrrhinus Saussure, 1860 (Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) with the description of four new species. Fieldiana Zoology, New Series 105: 1 - 53." type="book chapter" year="2005">Velazco, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L." pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="329 - 342" refId="ref35907" refString="Gardner, A. L. 2008 d (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Platyrrhinus Saussure, 1860. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 329 - 342. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gardner, 2008d</bibRefCitation>
). Measurements of our specimens fall within the range reported for the species.
</paragraph>
